==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Time signature
<hw>Time signature</hw>. <fld>(Music)</fld> <def>A sign at the beginning
of a composition or movement, placed after the key signature, to
indicate its time or meter. Also called <altname>rhythmical
signature</altname>. It is in the form of a fraction, of which the
denominator indicates the kind of note taken as time unit for the beat,
and the numerator, the number of these to the measure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

